Paper: hep-th/9301008

Date: 1993-01-04

Title: A Simple Method for Computing Soliton Statistics

Authors: Donald Spector

Comments: 9 pages, harvmac, HWS-92/09. (Added substantial details in one

section.)Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A9 (1994) 2245-2251

I provide an extremely simple argument that the kink-type solitons in certaintheories are fermionic. The argument is based on the Witten index, but can infact be used to determine soliton statistics in non-supersymmetric theories aswell.